sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    actor U as User
    participant FE as Frontend UI
    participant WP as WalletProvider
    participant W as Wallet
    participant API as Ktor Backend
    participant R as Redis
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant S as Sandbox Cluster
    participant J as SubmissionJudgeWorker
    participant SW as CompetitionSettlementWorker
    participant CHAIN as BlockchainTestContract

    Note over FE,API: 1. Platform metadata and login
    U->>FE: Open app / click Login
    FE->>API: GET /platform/meta
    API-->>FE: chainId, network, contract addresses
    FE->>API: POST /auth/challenge
    API->>R: store auth challenge
    API-->>FE: challenge payload
    FE->>WP: request wallet login
    WP->>W: request accounts + sign challenge
    W-->>WP: walletAddress + signature
    WP-->>FE: signed login payload
    FE->>API: POST /auth/verify
    API->>DB: create/load user
    API->>R: store auth session
    API-->>FE: authenticated session

    Note over FE,S: 2. Create problem validation preview
    U->>FE: Click Run test / Run all on create screen
    FE->>API: POST /problems/create/validate
    API->>S: run reference solution on one sandbox node
    S-->>API: expected output + runtime + memory
    API-->>FE: validation result

    Note over FE,CHAIN: 3. Create problem on-chain
    U->>FE: Click Create problem
    FE->>API: POST /problems/create/prepare
    API->>R: store short-lived create intent
    API->>CHAIN: prepare createCompetition calldata and value
    API-->>FE: tx target + calldata + value (+ optional approve)
    alt ERC-20 payment asset
        FE->>WP: send approve transaction
        WP->>W: eth_sendTransaction
        W->>CHAIN: approve(proxy, amount)
        CHAIN-->>W: tx hash
        W-->>WP: tx hash
        WP-->>FE: tx hash
    end
    FE->>WP: send create transaction
    WP->>W: eth_sendTransaction
    W->>CHAIN: createCompetition + prize deposit or ERC-20 pull
    CHAIN-->>W: tx hash
    W-->>WP: tx hash
    WP-->>FE: tx hash
    FE->>WP: wait for receipt
    WP->>W: eth_getTransactionReceipt polling
    W-->>WP: receipt
    WP-->>FE: confirmed receipt
    FE->>API: POST /problems/create/confirm
    API->>R: load and consume create intent
    API->>CHAIN: verify tx receipt and on-chain event
    API->>DB: insert problem + tests + on-chain metadata
    API-->>FE: created problem details

    Note over FE,CHAIN: 4. Join competition on-chain
    U->>FE: Click Join
    FE->>API: POST /problems/{id}/join/prepare
    API->>DB: load problem on-chain context
    API->>R: store short-lived join intent
    API->>CHAIN: prepare joinCompetition calldata and value
    API-->>FE: tx target + calldata + value (+ optional approve)
    alt ERC-20 payment asset
        FE->>WP: send approve transaction
        WP->>W: eth_sendTransaction
        W->>CHAIN: approve(proxy, amount)
        CHAIN-->>W: tx hash
        W-->>WP: tx hash
        WP-->>FE: tx hash
    end
    FE->>WP: send join transaction
    WP->>W: eth_sendTransaction
    W->>CHAIN: joinCompetition + entry fee deposit or ERC-20 pull
    CHAIN-->>W: tx hash
    W-->>WP: tx hash
    WP-->>FE: tx hash
    FE->>WP: wait for receipt
    WP->>W: eth_getTransactionReceipt polling
    W-->>WP: receipt
    WP-->>FE: confirmed receipt
    FE->>API: POST /problems/{id}/join/confirm
    API->>R: load and consume join intent
    API->>CHAIN: verify tx receipt and on-chain event
    API->>DB: insert participant + join tx metadata
    API-->>FE: joined

    Note over FE,S: 5. Run code preview
    U->>FE: Click Run
    FE->>API: POST /problems/{id}/run
    API->>DB: load problem tests and limits
    API->>S: run on one sandbox node
    S-->>API: test results + runtime + memory
    API-->>FE: preview result

    Note over FE,J: 6. Submit code and async judge
    U->>FE: Click Submit
    FE->>API: POST /problems/{id}/submit
    API->>DB: create problem_submission_judge_job
    API->>R: enqueue judge job id
    API-->>FE: jobId

    loop Poll job status
        FE->>API: GET /problems/submission-jobs/{jobId}
        API->>DB: read job status / preview / final result
        API-->>FE: queued / running / accepted / rejected / failed
    end

    J->>R: dequeue next job id
    J->>DB: load queued job
    J->>DB: load problem tests and submission context
    J->>S: run on all sandbox nodes
    S-->>J: outputs + suite runtime + memory + attestations
    J->>J: verify consensus and node attestations

    alt All tests passed and consensus reached
        J->>DB: insert submission + test results + attestations
        J->>CHAIN: recordSubmissionResult(hashes, runtime, memory, sandboxImageHash)
        CHAIN-->>J: result tx receipt
        J->>DB: save on-chain record tx
        J->>DB: mark judge job accepted
    else Tests failed
        J->>DB: mark judge job rejected + save preview test results
    else Consensus, registry, or infra error
        J->>DB: mark judge job failed
    end

    Note over SW,CHAIN: 7. Automatic competition settlement after deadline
    SW->>DB: fetch competitions pending settlement
    SW->>DB: fetch best accepted submission candidate
    alt Winner exists
        SW->>CHAIN: settleCompetition(competitionId)
        CHAIN-->>SW: settlement tx hash
        SW->>DB: save winner + settlement status
    else No valid winner or cancellation condition
        SW->>CHAIN: cancelCompetition(competitionId)
        CHAIN-->>SW: cancellation tx hash
        SW->>DB: save cancelled settlement status
    end

    Note over CHAIN,U: BlockchainTestContract keeps prize, entry fees, accepted result hashes, runtime, memory, payout/refund logic, and ETH/ERC-20 settlement rules on-chain.
